@page "/"

<PageTitle>ModernMediator — Blazor WASM</PageTitle>

<h1>ModernMediator Blazor WebAssembly Sample</h1>

<p>
    This sample demonstrates <strong>ModernMediator</strong> running entirely client-side in the
    browser via Blazor WebAssembly. Queries are dispatched from <code>@@code</code> blocks with
    zero server roundtrips — all mediator pipeline processing happens in the browser.
</p>

<div class="alert alert-success">
    <strong>AOT Compatible:</strong> ModernMediator uses compile-time
    source generation with zero runtime reflection in dispatch code.
    To publish with AOT enabled, add
    &lt;RunAOTCompilation&gt;true&lt;/RunAOTCompilation&gt;
    to the .csproj and run <code>dotnet publish -c Release</code>.
</div>

<div class="alert alert-primary">
    <strong>What to try:</strong> Navigate to the
    <a href="/animals">Animals</a> page to see mediator dispatch in action.
    Open browser developer tools (F12) to see <code>LoggingBehavior</code> output in the console.
</div>
